<TITLE> Deputy secy, family beaten at home </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 12 (bdnews24.com)A gang of miscreants beat a deputy secretary at the defence ministry and his family at his Azimpur staff quarters home early on Tuesday. Lalbagh police said some six masked miscreants entered Rafiul Alam's ground-floor flat at around 3:30am, cutting open the grills and beat him, his wife Meena Alam and daughters Rifat Ara and Taslima Alam. They were first admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital and then to another hospital that police could not name. Lalbagh police sub-inspector 'Imran' told bdnews24.com that the miscreants looted nothing but a gold chain of Meena Alam. No-one was arrested until afternoon after Rafiul filed a case. bd
